I guess we can start this chapter off by saying that wizardhood
isn't a right, it's a privilege, although it's not a privilege that
cannot be attained by anyone who is willing to follow a few simple
rules.  First-- to become a wizard you must be at a minimum level 20,
and, you must have completed all the required quests.  From a game
mechanics standpoint that is all that is really required.  From
the people standpoint what we don't want in our wizards are people who:
 
1.Cheat
  This could be anything from players who find bugs and don't report them
  but use them to their advantage;  players who are aware of loopholes
  in the security of the game and use them to either their benefit or
  the muds detrament.  Minor infractions will result in a warning, but
  major infractions or repeated infractions will make the chances of
  ever becoming a wizard almost non-existant.
 
2.Foul-Mouthed *#@&*(^&%
  People who are unable to speak to others without insulting half the
  mud in the process or are unable to speak without swearing every
  other word are not people we want here, and certainly will never be
  granted the privilege of becoming a wizard.
 
3.Lazy people.
  Darkwind currently is a fairly new mud, and we would like to get more
  areas open.  So if you don't plan on doing anything as a wizard we would
  prefer you stayed a player.  And, in actuality, if it appears you are not
  doing anything on your own, you will most likely be given something to
  do.
 
What do we want to see in our wizards?
1] basically the opposite of the traits listed above.
 
Darkwind is currently a little on the light side of normal wizards, and
if you are a motivated person who is able to do quality work, you will
like being here.  We are very liberal with our promotions and if you
show us you like it here we want to do our best to make you happy here
as well.

